{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\nouicompat\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Calibri;}{\f1\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}} {\colortbl ;\red79\green129\blue189;\red0\green0\blue255;} {\*\generator Riched20 10.0.18362}\viewkind4\uc1 \pard\qc\cf1\f0\fs32 Welcome to the i-Tree Eco Data Import Wizard\cf0\fs20\par
\pard\f1\fs18\par \f0\fs20 This wizard will guide you through the steps needed to import your data into Eco.\par \par Before you proceed you should make sure any data being imported is formatted consistently. If importing from Microsoft Excel, each column should be formatted according to the type of data it contains; mixing data types within a column may cause inconsistent results. For example, Microsoft Excel often displays data as numbers but actually formats them as text or string data. This will become apparent during the import process and should be fixed in Excel beforehand.\par \par \b Special Note:\b0 If you have empty cells in any of the first 10 rows, make sure you put appropriate "filler" values in them so that their data type can be inferred correctly. Example: Place 0's in numeric columns so that those cells are not improperly read as text values.\par \par Due to memory limitations, you may need to break large data sets into smaller batches.\par \par Where applicable, you can import your own ID numbers into the User ID field so you can cross reference your data later.\par \par A video tutorial about the process is available at: {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK http://www.itreetools.org/media/watch.php?m3riZhE_uSg }}{\fldrslt{http://www.itreetools.org/media/watch.php?m3riZhE_uSg\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20\par }

data.name: chkNeedMapValue.Text
data.value: I need to map my source column values to the Eco field values. (This comes later.)

data.name: label2.Text
data.value: Select a row to begin matching data:

data.name: label1.Text
data.value: Select a column below and then define how to import it into Eco. Repeat for EACH column BEFORE clicking Next.

data.name: lblSourceData.Text
data.value: Match your data by selecting the row and then clicking its empty Eco Value cell. Either enter a value or, for some data, search for or select the best match in the pop-up list.

data.name: richTextLabel1.RichText
lblSelectFile.Text
data.value: Select the file containing the data you'd like to import.

data.name: lblFinish.Text
data.value:
Click Finish to complete the import process or click Back to revise your settings and reprocess your data.
Please review your data after clicking Finish. Additional modifications may be required to meet your project specific requirements.
